

The files provided here are meant to give an exemple of the file formats used 
in a typical siestart run. As they were taken from different runs simulating 
different systems, they are not currently meant to be compatible with each 
other. It is the user's responsibility to adapt them to his own needs and 
calculation architecture.  




# bharat debugging
siesta_force.f90: 
 integer, parameter :: FSIESTA = 21
  real*8, parameter :: ZERO = 0.0d0
  character(len=20) :: SIESTA   = 'art2siesta'
  character(len=20) :: SIESTAFORCE = 'siesta2art'








